commit.message:
Handle another indexing case from NumPy

NumPy arrays of integers have an __index__ method -- it's meant to apply
to scalars, and it raises an error if you actually try to run it on an
array.

These arrays are iterable, so if we move the is_iterable check first,
we won't encounter this error.

commit.message:
Trim trailing white space from .travis.yml

Many editors clean up trailing white space on save. By removing it all
in one go, it helps keep future diffs cleaner by avoiding spurious white
space changes on unrelated lines.
